{
  "texts": [
    "Evaluating inter-rater reliability in skill level annotation.",
    "In video-based annotation, we analyzed inter-rater reliability across three skill levels: beginner, intermediate, and expert.",
    "Inter-rater reliability refers to the extent of agreement or consistency among different raters or annotators when assessing or scoring the same dataset.",
    "We calculated the inter-rater reliability between two coaches and among three coaches using Cohen's kappa and Fleiss' kappa values, respectively.",
    "Cohen's kappa is a statistic used to measure the agreement between two raters, going beyond mere chance agreement."
  ]
}